  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Total Knee Arthroplasty tibial tray fixation credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA-based prediction of tibial tray micromotion and bone-implant interface stress in a Class II total knee arthroplasty (TKA) device under physiological loading. COU1 evaluates whether the finite-element model can identify worst-case fixation failure conditions for a cementless tibial tray at Model Risk Level 3. Full 13-factor assessment: all 13 factors assessed with requiredLevel and achievedLevel populated; achievedLevel meets or exceeds requiredLevel for every factor. Inline AcceptanceCriteria linked per assessed factor. Sensitivity analysis documented over bone density and loading direction variations. Complete-profile orthopedic pathway NC-4 archetype.",
