        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — mesh convergence study",
        "description": "Systematic mesh refinement study (coarse, medium, fine, very fine) performed on tibial tray–bone interface region. Peak micromotion and von Mises stress at the keel tip must converge to within 5% between fine and very fine meshes (Richardson extrapolation applied). Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for the QoI must be < 3%."
      },
      "rationale": "Four-level mesh refinement study conducted (element edge lengths 4 mm, 2 mm, 1 mm, 0.5 mm at interface). Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI of 1.9% for peak micromotion and 2.3% for keel-tip von Mises stress. Achieved level 4 reflects formal GCI documentation exceeding MRL 3 requirement."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-tka-test-conditions",
