        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria — micromotion prediction vs RSA measurement",
        "description": "FEA-predicted peak micromotion must agree with RSA-measured micromotion within ±25 µm or 20% of measured value (whichever is larger) across all specimens. Normalized root-mean-square error (NRMSE) across the specimen population must be < 15%."
      },
      "rationale": "FEA vs RSA comparison across 8 specimens: mean absolute error 18.3 µm (14.2% of mean measured value). NRMSE 11.7%. All individual specimen predictions within ±25 µm acceptance band. Output comparison documented in Validation Report VR-TKA-2025-07."
    },
    {
