      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-tka-validation-relevance",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation relevance acceptance criteria — cadaveric model fidelity to COU",
        "description": "Validation scenario must use the same tibial tray geometry and material as the COU device. Bone surrogates or cadaveric specimens must represent the target patient population bone quality range. Loading conditions must span the physiological envelope defined in the operating envelope (1500–3000 N axial, ±5° rotation)."
      },
      "rationale": "Validation used production-intent tibial tray geometry (size 5, same CAD as submission device). Cadaveric bone density range (Singh II–III) overlaps with target population. Loading matrix covered 1500 N, 2100 N, and 2800 N axial loads with ±3° and ±5° rotation. Validation relevance gap analysis documented in VRGA-TKA-2025-02."
    },
