        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-tka-model-form",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — constitutive model selection for bone and implant",
        "description": "Cortical bone modeled as transversely isotropic linear elastic (E_axial = 17 GPa, E_transverse = 11.5 GPa) per Reilly & Burstein (1975). Trabecular bone modeled as isotropic linear elastic with density-dependent modulus per Morgan et al. (2003) power law. Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) modeled as isotropic linear elastic (E = 114 GPa). Model form selection must be justified against literature and scope of loading (sub-yield)."
      },
      "rationale": "All loading conditions confirmed sub-yield (maximum von Mises stress in bone < 60% of yield strength). Linear elastic constitutive models appropriate and justified per literature. Density-dependent trabecular modulus calibrated against CT-derived bone mineral density map. Model form justification documented in MFJ-TKA-2025-01."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-tka-model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-tka-model-inputs",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — material properties and geometric fidelity",
        "description": "Implant geometry reconstructed from production CAD files (tolerance ±0.05 mm). Bone geometry reconstructed from CT scans at ≤ 0.5 mm slice thickness. Material property sources must be peer-reviewed with documented uncertainty ranges. Interface friction coefficient (µ = 0.4–0.6) must be supported by tribological literature for Ti-6Al-4V on cortical bone."
      },
      "rationale": "Implant geometry imported directly from production CAD (STEP format, verified against drawing tolerances). CT reconstruction at 0.3 mm slice thickness. All material property values sourced from peer-reviewed literature with ±1σ uncertainty ranges tabulated. Interface friction coefficient µ = 0.5 selected per Dammak et al. (1994); sensitivity analysis confirmed results insensitive to µ ∈ [0.4, 0.6]."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-tka-test-samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
