        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test samples acceptance criteria — cadaveric specimen representativeness",
        "description": "Minimum 6 cadaveric tibiae spanning Singh grades II–III. Specimens must be sourced from donors aged 55–80 years. BMI range 20–35 kg/m². No prior knee surgery or metabolic bone disease. Specimen demographics must be documented and compared against target patient population."
      },
      "rationale": "Eight cadaveric tibiae used (Singh grades II: n=5, III: n=3). Donor age range 58–76 years (mean 67). BMI range 22–33 kg/m². No prior knee surgery confirmed by medical history review. Specimen demographics documented in Specimen Characterization Report SCR-TKA-2025-01."
    },
