        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-tka-equivalency",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters acceptance criteria — validation-to-COU parameter mapping",
        "description": "Formal parameter equivalency matrix must map each validation scenario input to the corresponding COU input, identifying any gaps. For each gap, a documented bridging argument or additional sensitivity analysis must demonstrate that the gap does not materially affect the QoI prediction within the COU operating envelope."
      },
      "rationale": "Parameter equivalency matrix PEM-TKA-2025-01 completed. Key gap identified: validation specimens limited to size 5 implant; COU spans sizes 3–7. Bridging sensitivity analysis (sizes 3, 5, 7 simulated) confirmed peak micromotion varies < 8% across size range at matched bone density, within QoI acceptance tolerance. Gap formally accepted in decision record."
